Basic question:
I have a style field for text-alignment on a custom module. How do I pull in the value from the hubL variable into the module?

I tried adding this to module.css
```.button-container {
  text-align: {{ module.style.textalignment_field }};
}
  ```
but I think I'm not grokking how to use the variable to create css. (I did try rendering the variable as text and saw that it then shows as a list of 2 values, one for inline styling and one for css i think.)

```.button-container {
  {{ module.style.textalignment_field.css }}
}```

I don't think I'm filtering this right. I created a Related Posts module and I'd like to have it populate only tags the same as the blog post itself:

```          {% set current_post_tags = blog_recent_tag_posts %}
          {% related_blog_posts limit=3, no_wrapper=True, post_formatter="recent_post", tags="current_post_tags" %}```
